## Security & Auth

### JWT Auth Migration Complete

All router authentication migrated from API keys to JWT:

| Router | Auth Type | Status |
|--------|-----------|--------|
| `routers/admin.py` | AdminDep | ✅ Migrated |
| `routers/client.py` | ClientDep | ✅ Migrated |
| `routers/miner.py` | MinerDep | ✅ Migrated |
| `routers/services.py` | ClientDep | ✅ Migrated |
| `contexts/hermes/*.py` | AdminDep | ✅ Migrated (5 files) |
| `contexts/agent_coordination/*.py` | AdminDep | ✅ Migrated (2 files) |
| `contexts/bounty/*.py` | AuthDep | ✅ Migrated |
| `contexts/ecosystem/*.py` | AuthDep | ✅ Migrated |

### Deprecation Warnings

`apps/coordinator-api/src/app/deps.py` now emits `DeprecationWarning` for all legacy API key functions:
- `require_client_key()` → Use `ClientDep`
- `require_miner_key()` → Use `MinerDep`
- `require_admin_key()` → Use `AdminDep`
- `get_miner_id()` → Use `MinerDep`
- `APIKeyValidator` → Use role-based dependencies

### CI Enforcement

Removed `continue-on-error: true` from all CI jobs:
- ✅ Lint (ruff)
- ✅ Format check (black)
- ✅ Type check (mypy)
- ✅ Tests (pytest)
- ✅ Security scans (bandit, semgrep, trufflehog)

